      <h1 class="mb-4">üßô‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Restmancer API ‚Äì Blog Endpoints</h1>
        <p>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-info btn-sm mb-4">üîô Back to Homepage</a>
        </p>
      <p>This page documents the available REST endpoints for fetching blog post data from the Restmancer API.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>GET <code>/api/blogs</code></h2>
      <p>Returns a list of blog posts. If the <code>limit</code> is greater than initial data length (10), more will be generated on the fly.</p>
      <h5>Optional Query Parameters:</h5>
      <ul>
        <li><code>limit</code> ‚Äì Number of blogs to return.</li>
        <li><code>field</code> ‚Äì Comma-separated list of fields (e.g., <code>title,content</code>).</li>
      </ul>
      <h6>Examples:</h6>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/api/blogs" target="_blank">/api/blogs</a></li>
        <li><a href="/api/blogs?limit=5" target="_blank">/api/blogs?limit=5</a></li>
        <li><a href="/api/blogs?field=title,slug&limit=3" target="_blank">/api/blogs?field=title,slug&limit=3</a></li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h2>üìÇ Example Fields Available</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>id</code></li>
        <li><code>title</code></li>
        <li><code>slug</code></li>
        <li><code>author</code> (object with <code>id</code>, <code>name</code>, <code>email</code>)</li>
        <li><code>content</code></li>
        <li><code>tags</code></li>
        <li><code>createAt</code></li>
        <li><code>likes</code></li>
        <li><code>comments</code> (array of objects with <code>id</code>, <code>author</code>, <code>content</code>, <code>postedAt</code>)</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="info-box">
        <p>
          You can control the number of blogs returned and which fields are included using
          query parameters like <code>?limit=3</code> and <code>?field=title,slug</code>.
        </p>
        <p>Example: <code>GET /api/blogs?field=title,slug&limit=3</code></p>
